decision d_33847bd84f6f0881 target=file subject=crates/queue/src/dkim.rs status=accepted source="human:justin" basis=- title="Publish DKIM p= as X.509 SPKI DER, not mail_auth's native PKCS#1 output" detail="DMARC aggregate report from google.com (susumu.dev, selector=litterae, 2026-07-19) showed dkim=fail while SPF passed. dig confirmed the published TXT record was syntactically well-formed DKIM1/k=rsa but decoded as a bare PKCS#1 RSAPublicKey DER (flat SEQUENCE{INTEGER modulus, INTEGER exponent}, 270 bytes) rather than X.509 SubjectPublicKeyInfo. Root cause: mail_auth::dkim::generate::DkimKeyPair::generate_rsa's public_key() calls to_pkcs1_der(), and litterae's dns_txt_record() base64'd that directly. mail_auth's own verifier code tries SPKI first and only falls back to PKCS#1, confirming SPKI is the real-world-expected format; Google's verifier evidently isn't lenient about it. Fix: dns_txt_record() now re-encodes public_der through rsa::pkcs1::DecodeRsaPublicKey -> rsa::pkcs8::EncodePublicKey before publishing, added rsa as a direct queue dependency for this. Private key / signing path (RsaKey::from_key_der(PrivateKeyDer::Pkcs1)) is untouched -- only the DNS-facing encoding changed. Operator action still required: republish the corrected TXT record at litterae._domainkey.susumu.dev from the admin panel; the DKIM key itself was not rotated, only its published encoding.";
decision d_2f69778030e79ae1 target=file subject=web/src/lib/RichTextEditor.svelte status=accepted source="human:justin" basis=- title="Scope outline:none to TipTap's .ProseMirror div, not the wrapper" detail="User reported a visible border with no padding to the text when clicking into the compose body. Cause: editorEl (the styled px-4/py-3 wrapper) had outline-none, but TipTap/ProseMirror mounts its own contenteditable .ProseMirror div as a child of editorEl and that inner div is what actually receives focus -- it has no padding of its own, so the browser's default focus ring rendered flush against the text regardless of the wrapper's outline-none. Fixed by targeting :global(.tiptap-body .ProseMirror) directly.";
decision d_1fa2f8e52ea71c7f target=file subject=web/src/lib/composeState.svelte.ts status=accepted source="human:justin" basis=- title="Prepend an empty paragraph before the signature block in new/reply compose bodies" detail="User reported the signature sits at the very top of a new/reply compose body, forcing several Enter presses before typing. openNewMessage/openReply set bodyHtml = signatureBlockHtml() with nothing preceding it, so the signature WAS the entire initial document. Fixed via initialBodyHtml() = '<p></p>' + signatureBlockHtml(), giving the cursor a line to land on above the signature. Separately: replies currently include no quoted original message at all (openReply never inserts thread content) -- raised with the user whether to add quote-on-reply plus a collapse/show-more affordance for the quoted chain, matching common mail client behavior; not yet decided or built.";
